Description: A Watch with Style … No Matter What Color, It Is Incredible, and It is an AUTOMATIC ... No Winding and No Battery !!! Plus 3 Rubber Bands to Give You Different Looks Make It Yours and Enjoy for Years to Come !!! Stuhrling Original Women's Manchester Ozzie Sport Edition Interchangeable Strap Watch With three interchangeable straps, this exciting Stuhrling Original offering is perfect for any occasion! The design begins with a square 316L stainless steel case in yellow-tone. Stuhrling Original constructs a curved case for maximum comfort. A round exhibition back gives you an insider's view of the desirable Caliber ST-90050 Automatic movement with 20 jewels. A Krysterna crystal and a push and pull crown complete the case execution. The square case coordinating textured dial includes a circular skeletonized inner dial with multicolored Arabic numerals at all hour positions on the outer dial. Luminous black hour and minute hands, and a black seconds hand keeps you right on time. Stuhrling Original generously includes three interchangeable rubber straps (with quick change pins) in white, pink or black so you can change your look with ease. All straps attach comfortably with buckle clasps. Treat yourself or someone special to the gift of time today! Strap: Rubber = Black, White and Pink Movement: Caliber ST-90050 Automatic w/ 20 Jewels Crystal: Krysterna Crown: Push/Pull Clasp: Buckle Strap Measurements: 9-1/4" L x 22mm W Case Measurements: 37mm L x 38mm W Water Resistance: 5 ATM - 50 meters - 165 feet Warranty: Two year limited warranty provided by Stuhrling Original LLC, plus one year extension available through www.stuhrling.com for a total of three years. Additional Features: This watch comes packaged in a Stuhrling Original watch box with an instruction manual, warranty information and polishing cloth. About Krysterna: Developed for the high-end eyeglass industry, Krysterna is a synthetic transparent material which is distinguished by its extreme durability. Stuhrling Original was involved in Krysterna's early development and was one of the first watch makers to incorporate this physically powerful material into a timepiece as a crystal. Because Krysterna has more strength spread over a spread surface than sapphire, it is considered more shatter-resistant than a sapphire crystal. Make It Yours and Enjoy for Years and Years !!!
